title: Serendipity (The Show)
body:
Pairings: BTS x Reader/OT7 x reader

Summary: In a world where the biggest economical powers dominate the industry of the entertaiment humanity seems almost lost in the crecent sadism of the public. A company invents a revolutionary program. Six men and one woman enter an apartment, only two comes out alive. ¿What’s your choice?

Written By: @caosfueradecontexto

A/N: I like bangtan, sue me. 

“They say that the world was built for two

Only worth living if somebody is loving you

Baby, now you do”

Lana del Rey – Video Games

Chapter 1

You turned on the televisión, the chosen numbers winked on the screen and you sighed watching with absence the emotion of the audience. Your mother was serving dinnner and standing in front of the television with expectation. It was the solution that society had given to the lack of romance, televise arranged marriages at the risk of death. Every two months they choose a girl between 18 and 25 years, and they locked her away between four walls to entertain the population, waiting that she would’ve be able to find love under pressure. Most people enjoyed the show and even made bets choosing the right candidate. They played with existence and feelings of others as if they were laboratory rats.

Your mother looked at you out of the corner of her eye, smiling, it was your last year of being elegible, and you knew that within her there was hope that you were the chosen one, after all, the family of the participants lived under the most confortable conditions as the price to give away the lifes of their children.

The numbers changed on the screen until the last digit and your eyes opened up in surprise, your right hand holding your left wrist where the code itched against your skin. Your name shined on the screen and your mother turned to look at you with amazement.

- It’s you! - She screamed moving towars you with big steps to envolve you in a hug. - Aren’t you happy? - She asked watching your empty expression, there were tears in her face and you hided yourself in her chest, your father looked at you horrified and you could only shared the sentiment.

The lights in the room are too bright and your eyes are immediately resistant to light. You’re sitting in front of a man dressed in a black tuxedo and a briefcase on the table and you think you have seen his face before in publicities on the street but you can’t remember. For all that you know until this moment he could be one of the faces of the biggest industries of make up or clothes, he has the aura and the fake smile of conformism on his face. Behind him there’s a second and more taller man completely silent like a shadow.

- I’m Kim Seokjin. - Says the one you assumed is a model, and pauses as if waiting for the name to provoke something in you, it probably should, but you only look at him in silence. Strangely, he does not seem offended by it and his smile becomes brighter. - I’m a model for Hit Entertaiment. - He adds as a presentation, confirming your suspicions as you search between the files of your mind to recognise his face. - The field of my enterprise is pretty wide… - He procedes and it’s only then that you remember.

- You are the car door guy - You exclaim. Your mother has been talking about him for days, he’s the new presenter of the show.

Seokjin seems surprised for a second, but smiles again.

- Yeah that’s me - He says pointing him at himself and you just nod. He has the kind of face that will invite you to accept a deal for your soul. You can see why they picked him.

You can see their faces on the screen. The six man that are ready to undergo to the tortured of the reality show, and you have to questionate your sanity once again. They are all really handsome, but there’s nothing more you can say just by looking at their faces. Some of them seem too young. Seokjin’s voice interrups your thoughts as he walks in front of the screen.

- You’re going to meet them this afternoon and we will begin with the recordings. - You nodded looking at the boys faces again. Your heart compressed by pain as you try to visualize the end of the show. You have made it this dar, but you still don’t know if you are capable of going with it.

- Should i know something about them before seeing them? - You ask trying to memorize their faces. Is the best gift you can give them knowing you’re going to be the ending of each and every one of them.

- Their names? - Seokjin suggest. - You should show your interest in person when the cameras are on. - You sigh.

- If i ever get to feel interest at all.- Seokjin smiles but the smile doesn’t get to his eyes. He has stopped acting on your presence after you signed the contract.

- We’re gonna get them out alive - He talks as if he could read your mind putting a hand over your shoulder as a sign of support. - They’re the best agents that we have.
